The paper deals with path planning for unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in cluttered environments, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach uses a Gaussian Process (GP)-based model, which is a popular machine learning technique (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques for target detection (cs.CV). The adaptive replanning scheme involves trade-offs between different objectives, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using extensive simulations, which is a common practice in machine learning and robotics research (cs.LG).
